						<summary>

						<p>On a slab set up in the compound of the Kāśīviśvanātha temple.</p>						

						<p>Rudranāyaka Gaja-sāhiṇi, A.D. 1290.</p>						

						<p>Dated in Śaka 1212, uttarāyaṇa-sankrānti (= A.D. 1290).</p>						

						<p>Damaged. Registers a gift of land to god Chōḍa-Gōpīnātha of Oṅgōlu by the chief for the merit of his parents. Sāraṅga is mentioned as the <hi rend="italic">sthānika</hi> and Brammi-reḍḍi and others as signatories.</p>						

						<p>(Published in Butterworth &amp; Venugopal chetty. NDI, Part III, p. 1082 without separating the lines).</p>						

						</summary>
