<p>[Figures of Sun and Moon, and below are conch, deity (?) and discus.]</p>

<p>
<lb n="1"/>svasti śrī śakavaruṣaṁbulu 1212 
<lb n="2"/>yagu nēṁṭi yuttarāyaṇa nimitya 
<lb n="3" break="no"/>ṁbuna svasti śrīmanmahārāya gajā(ja) 
<lb n="4" break="no"/>sāhiṇi rudraya nāyaṁkulu ta 
<lb n="5" break="no"/>ma tallidaṁḍrulaku dharmmārtta(rttha)mugā 
<lb n="6" break="no"/>nu Oṁgōlani cōḍa gōpīnāthaniki cēnu 
<lb n="7"/>velivolamuku <unclear>14</unclear> <gap reason="lost" quantity="10" unit="character"/> 
<lb n="8"/><unclear>rca</unclear>nakugānu <gap reason="lost" quantity="10" unit="character"/> 
<lb n="9"/>sta(sthā)nikuḍu sāraṁguṁḍu dīniki <gap reason="lost" quantity="5" unit="character"/> <unclear>śā</unclear> 
<lb n="10"/>sanamu ḍasira brammire<unclear>ḍḍi</unclear>vu cēmanā 
<lb n="11" break="no"/>yuḍu pinnamareḍḍi perumāṁḍi re<unclear>ḍḍi</unclear> 
</p>

